{"title_page": "BhlA holin family", "text_new": "The '''BhlA Holin Family''' ([http://tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=1.E.27 TC# 1.E.27]) is named after putative [[holin]]-like peptides encoded in bacteria with [[bacteriocin]] similarities. BhlA proteins are generally about 67 to 80 amino acyl residues (aas) in length and exhibit a single N-terminal transmembrane segment (TMS). BhlA ([http://tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=1.E.27.1.4 TC# 1.E.27.1.4]). It has an antibacterial activity against [[Gram-positive bacteria]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Anthony|first=Thangamani|last2=Chellappa|first2=Gunasekaran Stalin|last3=Rajesh|first3=Thangamani|last4=Gunasekaran|first4=Paramasamy|date=2009-12-05|title=Functional analysis of a putative holin-like peptide-coding gene in the genome of Bacillus licheniformis AnBa9|journal=Archives of Microbiology|language=en|volume=192|issue=1|pages=51\u201356|doi=10.1007/s00203-009-0530-7|pmid=19967339|issn=0302-8933}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Aunpad|first=Ratchaneewan|last2=Panbangred|first2=Watanalai|date=2012-01-10|title=Evidence for Two Putative Holin-Like Peptides Encoding Genes of Bacillus pumilus Strain WAPB4|journal=Current Microbiology|language=en|volume=64|issue=4|pages=343\u2013348|doi=10.1007/s00284-011-0074-3|pmid=22231453|issn=0343-8651}}</ref> A representative list of proteins belonging to this family can be found in the [http://tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=1.E.27.1 Transporter Classification Database].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=1.E.27|title=1.E.27 The BhlA Holin (BhlA Holin) Family|website=TCDB|access-date=2016-03-30}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Holin]]\n* [[Lysin]]\n* [[Transporter Classification Database]]\n\n== Further reading ==\n* [https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/A8FGN0 \"BPUM_2741 - Uncharacterized protein - Bacillus pumilus (strain SAFR-032) - BPUM_2741 gene & protein\"]. ''www.uniprot.org''. Retrieved 2016-03-30.\n* {{cite journal | last1 = Wang | first1 = I. N. | last2 = Smith | first2 = D. L. | last3 = Young | first3 = R. | year = 2000 | title = Holins: the protein clocks of bacteriophage infections | url = | journal = Annual Review of Microbiology | volume = 54 | issue = 1| pages = 799\u2013825 | doi = 10.1146/annurev.micro.54.1.799 | pmid = 11018145 }}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Biology|border=no}}\n{{CCBYSASource|sourcepath=http://tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=1.E.27|sourcearticle=1.E.27 The BhlA Holin (BhlA Holin) Family|revision=699838558}}\n\n[[Category:Holins]]\n\n\n{{membrane-protein-stub}}\n", "text_old": "The '''BhlA Holin Family''' ([http://tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=1.E.27 TC# 1.E.27]) is named after putative [[holin]]-like peptides encoded in bacteria with [[bacteriocin]] similarities. BhlA proteins are generally about 67 to 80 amino acyl residues (aas) in length and exhibit a single N-terminal transmembrane segment (TMS). BhlA ([http://tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=1.E.27.1.4 TC# 1.E.27.1.4]). It has an antibacterial activity against [[Gram-positive bacteria]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Anthony|first=Thangamani|last2=Chellappa|first2=Gunasekaran Stalin|last3=Rajesh|first3=Thangamani|last4=Gunasekaran|first4=Paramasamy|date=2009-12-05|title=Functional analysis of a putative holin-like peptide-coding gene in the genome of Bacillus licheniformis AnBa9|journal=Archives of Microbiology|language=en|volume=192|issue=1|pages=51\u201356|doi=10.1007/s00203-009-0530-7|pmid=19967339|issn=0302-8933}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Aunpad|first=Ratchaneewan|last2=Panbangred|first2=Watanalai|date=2012-01-10|title=Evidence for Two Putative Holin-Like Peptides Encoding Genes of Bacillus pumilus Strain WAPB4|journal=Current Microbiology|language=en|volume=64|issue=4|pages=343\u2013348|doi=10.1007/s00284-011-0074-3|pmid=22231453|issn=0343-8651}}</ref> A representative list of proteins belonging to this family can be found in the [http://tcdb.org/search/result.php?tc=1.E.27.1 Transporter Classification Database].<ref>{{Cite web